joelib2.util
Class BasicProperty

java.lang.Object
  joelib2.util.BasicProperty
All Implemented Interfaces:
Property
public class BasicProperty
extends Object
implements Property

JOELib property representation.

Properties will be defined here for three reasons:

  1. Type checking, for all possible parameters you can imagine
  2. Is this an optional parameter entry ?
  3. Allow helper classes to access these data elements (easier)...

BasicProperty

public BasicProperty(String _name,
                     String _representation,
                     String _description,
                     boolean _optional)
Constructor for a JOELib property without default value.

The _representation defines the object type. Here are some examples 

 java.lang.Boolean      - Boolean
 [Ljava.lang.String;    - String array !!!
 java.lang.Integer      - Integer

Parameters:
_name - name of the parameter
_representation - data type (representation) of the parameter. Arrays looks like: '[Lclass;', e.g. '[Ljava.lang.String;'
_description - description of this parameter
_optional - true if this parameter is optional

Constructor for a JOELib property.

The _representation defines the object type. Here are some examples 

 java.lang.Boolean      - Boolean
 [Ljava.lang.String;    - String array !!!
 java.lang.Integer      - Integer

Parameters:
_name - name of the parameter
_representation - data type (representation) of the parameter. Arrays looks like: '[Lclass;', e.g. '[Ljava.lang.String;'.
_description - description of this parameter
_optional - true if this parameter is optional
_defaultProperty - default value of this parameter which must be of type _representation
